NBA 2K21 - Crossgen Edition
Optimized for PS5, Xbox Series X, PS4 and Xbox One and includes Timed Shot, Shot Profile, Four Shot Profiles and auto Dribble Moves. Be sure to read the instructions regarding online/offline timing.

 Introduction

The NBA 2K21 - Crossgen Edition GamePack features exclusive mods specially designed to work with all current and next-generation consoles. Awesome features include Timed Shot with Four Shot Profiles and Dribble Moves and Dribble Moves Types such as Momentum, Curry Slide, Explosive BTB, Momentum + Behind The Back, Momentum + Curryslide, Boost, Spinback, Speedboost to Curryslide, SpeedBoost at Angle, Momentum SPAM, Hand Crab, Hand Cross, Hand Momentum Curry, Hand Momentum BTB, Spin Back and Hand Spin Dunk. You will be unstoppable with this pack!

 How to Setup this GamePack

This GamePack is split into color-coded categories that makes setup and organization easy to follow and understand.
There are two methods to setup and configure Mods in this GamePack, the first being the GamePack Configuration Interface (or GCI) and the second is the Zen OLED Menu System.

â€‹
âš™
 GamePack Configuration Interface (GCI)

The GCI either pops up every time you program a GamePack to a memory slot, or when you click on the memory slot number in Zen Studio. This is a really quick way to setup all your preferred defaults from the get-go.
GamePack Default Settings: All default values are optimized for console gaming with a controller. If using
ðŸ–±
Mouse & keyboard, you should expect to have to change almost all default settings to suit your preferred playing style, in particular changing all in-game stick sensitivity settings to maximum.
It's very important that you setup your mouse before trying to use any GamePacks or scripts.
NBA2K21 - Crossgen Edition GamePack Configuration Interface (GCI)

â€‹
ðŸ”²
 Zen OLED Menu System

The Zen OLED Menu System is a new groundbreaking feature that allows the configuration and tuning of dozens of different Mod modes and combinations, on-the-fly and in seconds, all from an easy to read OLED interface. Once you have programmed this GamePack to a memory slot it must be enabled and active. This is done by pressing the Memory Slot Button (P1) until the logo of the GamePack you wish to use appears on the OLED screen.
When you see the logo of this GamePack displayed on the screen, simply hold LT/L2 & press MENU/OPTIONS to access the Mod Menu System.
Community GamePack OLED Menu System Quick Toggle: HOLD LT/L2 & PRESS MENU/OPTIONS
Community GamePack OLED Mod Menu System
All Adjustable Mods can be tuned and tested in real-time directly from the Zen GamePack OLED Adjustables Menu.

 Screensaver

The Zen OLED Menu System has built in screensaver protection to help protect against screen burn. It will kick in after 3 minutes of inactivity. Press any button to return to the Mod Menu screen.

 In-Game Settings

These are all of the settings required for the Mods to function correctly, and they also allow you to dramatically improve the quality and accuracy of your characters movement.

â€‹
 In-Game Controller Vibration

This option blocks all rumble signals sent from the game, but still allows the GamePack to read in-game rumble frequencies which is used by several mods to measure timing. The In-Game Controller Vibration option must always be enabled.
This step is critical. If you don't enable In-Game Controller Vibration, several Mods in this GamePack may not function correctly.
  1. 1.
    Press the MENU/OPTION button on your controller
  2. 2.
    Go to OPTIONS & TAP 2x TIMES TO CONTROLLER SETTINGS
  3. 3.
    Select VIBRATION

 Timed Shot

Timed Shot is a mod which will release a shot after a specified amount of time while holding X (Xbox) or Square (PS4).
Stats, badges, player, your position on the court, character animation, jumpshot, and whether you are playing online or offline will affect both your timing or consistency of this mod.
Please note that while the Timed Shot mod does work online, it may be inconsistent with some users who have poor latency with their connection to the game servers. Offline mode will of course be the same consistency for everyone.
Each shot has three variables that can be adjusted to account for the three supported Jumpshots (Standing, Catch + Shoot, and Running). It is important to know that your position on the court will effect the timing of your shot the most. Included in this GamePack are Four Shot Profiles and it is recommended to set each one for a different spot you prefer to shoot from.
For each profile we recommend the four following locations two point, corners, at the top of the 3 point line, the middle of the center circle and three point line.

Setup Timed Shot

To setup your timed shot you will need to pick a location you would like to shoot from. For this example, we'll go with a shot taken from inside the two point zone. This is the area inside of the two point zone and not including the free throw area. Now follow these step-by-step instructions
ðŸ‘‰
  1. 1.
    Make sure your player is standing still. It doesn't matter if they are dribbling or holding the ball.
  2. 2.
    Enable the Timed Shot mod and hold X / Square. Your shot will either display as 'Late' or 'Early' in-game.
  3. 3.
    Press and hold LT / L2 & Menu / Options then enter 'Adjustables' in the GamePack LED menu.
  4. 4.
    If your shot is showing as late decrease the time or increase if the time is showing as late for Standing in the Profile you are using (Default is Profile 1 / Standing JS P1)
  5. 5.
    Once you are getting 'Excellent' when shooting, you will need to set the time for Catch + Shoot.
  6. 6.
    While Standing in the same spot, have the ball passed to your player and as soon as the ball is caught hold X / Square.
  7. 7.
    Repeat the adjusting you did in Step 4 until 'Excellent' is displayed.
  8. 8.
    All that is left is to set up the Running variable. To do this make sure you are sprinting and hold X / Square once your player is in the spot you want to shoot from (two point area in the tutorial) and repeat Step 4 until 'Excellent' is displayed.
  9. 9.
    Press B / Circle to exit the Menu and the values will be saved to the memory in the Zen.
Please note that while this shot does work online, it may be inconsistent with some users who have poor latency with their connection to the game servers. Offline mode will of course be the same consistency for everyone.
Set a time specially for your shot, and when that time has passed the ball will be thrown. Keep in mind when using this mod online you may need to change the timing based on your connection/ping

 Shot Profile

Select the Shot Profile to use. Set custom timing for Standing, Catch + Shoot, and Running values for each available profile
To set up Shot Profiles, open the GamePack Menu and switch to a different Profile. From here simply repeat the steps above for each different profile and you are all set. When playing you are able to quickly toggle to another profile to load in the values for the spots on the court you just configured.

 Dribble Moves

When enabled this will you to click the left or right stick to perform a selected advance dribble with ease. Dual Dribble only works with Xbox One / Series X|S. This allows you to have 1 move on each stick and the MOD will automatically know which hand the ball is in to trigger the correct dribble move. While enabled hold the right trigger and press DOWN DPAD for a Takeover. While disabled press RS for a steal. Hold right trigger and press L3/LS to perform a Quick Stop.
When enabled this will you to click the left or right stick to perform a selected advance dribble with ease. Dual Dribble only works with Xbox One / Series X|S. This allows you to have 1 move on each stick and the MOD will automatically know which hand the ball is in to trigger the correct dribble move. While enabled hold the right trigger and press DOWN DPAD for a Takeover. While disabled press RS for a steal. Hold right trigger and press L3/LS to perform a Quick Stop. You may assign 2 sets of move when not using Dual Dribble. One set when holding the right trigger and pressing either analog stick and another set when you are not using the right trigger. If Dual Dribble is enabled this doubles to 4 sets of dribble moves.
Quick Stop is a mod that can be toggled when holding both triggers and the left stick. Then while doing so press RS / R3 to toggle the mod on and off. While active press either LS / L3 or RS / R3 to perform a quick stop.
Dual Dribble is for Xbox Series X|S and Xbox One only.

 Crossover Auto-Remap

When this GamePack is being used on a PlayStation 5 or 4 and detects the connected controller is not a DualSense or DualShock 4, it will automatically reassign Touchpad to the Select/Back/View/Minus Button of your crossover controller so you are still able to utilize the Touchpad functionality on a PlayStation while using a Crossover controller. You can also access the PS5/PS4 Share Screen by pressing Select/Back/View/Minus + RS (Right Stick).

Troubleshooting

If you are experiencing unstable performance or settings issues with your GamePack, it's likely that the configuration profile has become corrupted. This can sometimes happen when updating to a newer GamePack version with major structural changes or using a memory slot that already had a pack previously programmed to it.
Simply go to Device
ðŸ‘‰
 Erase Memory Slots, unplug the Zen mini-USB cable, go to File
ðŸ‘‰
 Relaunch as Admin, reconnect the mini-USB cable to the Zen, and program the GamePack again. You will now find the Mods are working as they should
